[1;4mConfiguration reference[0m

This topic contains the full repository configuration reference for nextest.

This reference is also available [34;4m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/reference/\on the nextest site[0m]8;;\.

For more information about how repository configuration works, see the [34;4m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/\main]8;;\[0m
[34;4m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/\configuration page[0m]8;;\.

[1;4mConfiguration file locations[0m

Configuration is loaded in the following order (higher priority overrides
lower):

1. Repository config ([36m.config/nextest.toml[0m)
2. Tool-specific configs (specified via [36m--tool-config-file[0m)
3. Default embedded config

Tool-specific configs allow tools to provide their own nextest configuration
that integrates with repository settings.

For more information about configuration hierarchy, see [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/#hierarchical-configuration\Hierarchical]8;;\[0m
[34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/#hierarchical-configuration\configuration[0m]8;;\.

[1;4mRepository configuration schema[0m

[3m(since 0.9.134)[0m

A JSON Schema is available for nextest's repository configuration. The schema
can be obtained through:

- For the latest released version of nextest, at
  [34;4m[36m]8;;https://nexte.st/schemas/repo-config.json\https://nexte.st/schemas/repo-config.json[0m]8;;\. This URL is updated with new
  nextest releases.
- For the schema corresponding to a particular version of nextest, by running
  [36mcargo nextest self schema repo-config[0m.

The schema can be used:

- To validate a repository configuration file.
- With the [34;4m]8;;https://tombi-toml.github.io/tombi\Tombi[0m]8;;\ language server for TOML or [34;4m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/integrations/rustrover/\RustRover[0m]8;;\, to provide autocomplete
  in supported IDEs and editors. (The taplo language server is not supported due
  to a [34;4m]8;;https://github.com/tamasfe/taplo/pull/779\crash bug[0m]8;;\.)

Note that the schema is somewhat stricter than nextest's own config parser:
unknown configuration items will fail schema validation, while nextest itself
will only print out a warning.

The schema is part of the [34;4m]8;;https://www.schemastore.org/\JSON Schema Store[0m]8;;\, so both Tombi and RustRover will
automatically download it for you. Because nextest's configuration (outside of
experimental configuration) is [34;4m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/stability/\append-only[0m]8;;\, the schema will automatically be
updated as new nextest versions are released.

[1;4mTop-level configuration[0m

These parameters are specified at the root level of the configuration file.

[1;4m[36mnextest-version[0m

[3m(since 0.9.55)[0m

- [1mType[0m: String or object
- [1mDescription[0m: The minimum required (and optionally recommended) version of
  nextest for this configuration.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/minimum-versions/\Minimum nextest versions]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: Unset (the minimum version check is disabled)
- [1mExamples[0m:
      nextest-version = [32m"0.9.50"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      nextest-version = { required = [32m"0.9.20"[0m, recommended = [32m"0.9.30"[0m }

[1;4m[36mexperimental[0m

- [1mType[0m: Array of strings
- [1mDescription[0m: Enables experimental, non-stable features.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/setup-scripts/\Setup scripts[0m]8;;\, [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/wrapper-scripts/\wrapper scripts]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m[][0m (no experimental features enabled)
- [1mValid values[0m:
  - [36m"setup-scripts"[0m [3m(since 0.9.98)[0m (originally [3m(since 0.9.59)[0m)
  - [36m"wrapper-scripts"[0m [3m(since 0.9.98)[0m

- [1mExample[0m:
      experimental = [[32m"setup-scripts"[0m]

[1;4m[36mstore[0m

- [1mType[0m: Object
- [1mDescription[0m: Configuration for the nextest store directory.

[1;4m[36mstore.dir[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (path)
- [1mDescription[0m: Directory where nextest stores its data.
- [1mDefault[0m: [36mtarget/nextest[0m

[1;4mProfile configuration[0m

Profiles are configured under [36m[profile.<name>][0m. The default profile is called
[36m[profile.default][0m.

[1;4mGeneral configuration[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.inherits[0m

[3m(since 0.9.115)[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: The profile to inherit settings from.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/#profile-inheritance\Profile inheritance]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"default"[0m

[1;4mCore test execution[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.default-filter[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (filterset expression)
- [1mDescription[0m: The default set of tests run by [36mcargo nextest run[0m, as a filterset
  expression.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/selecting/#running-a-subset-of-tests-by-default\Running a subset of tests by default]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"all()"[0m (all tests are run)
- [1mExample[0m: [36mdefault-filter = "not test(very_slow_tests)"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.global-timeout[0m

[3m(since 0.9.100)[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (duration)
- [1mDescription[0m: A global timeout for the entire test run.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/features/slow-tests/#setting-a-global-timeout\Setting a global timeout]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: Unset (no global timeout)
- [1mExample[0m: [36mglobal-timeout = "2h"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.test-threads[0m

- [1mType[0m: Integer or string
- [1mDescription[0m: Number of threads to run tests with.
- [1mValid values[0m: Positive integer, negative integer (relative to CPU count), or
  [36m"num-cpus"[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"num-cpus"[0m
- [1mExample[0m: [36mtest-threads = 4[0m or [36mtest-threads = "num-cpus"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.threads-required[0m

- [1mType[0m: Integer or string
- [1mDescription[0m: Number of threads each test reserves from the pool.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/threads-required/\Heavy tests and [36mthreads-required]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m: Positive integer, [36m"num-cpus"[0m, or [36m"num-test-threads"[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m1[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.run-extra-args[0m

[3m(since 0.9.86)[0m

- [1mType[0m: Array of strings
- [1mDescription[0m: Extra arguments to pass to test binaries.
