      [2m# or[0m
      retries = { backoff = [32m"fixed"[0m, count = [33m3[0m, delay = [32m"1s"[0m }
      [2m# or[0m
      retries = { backoff = [32m"exponential"[0m, count = [33m4[0m, delay = [32m"2s"[0m, max-delay = [32m"10s"[0m, jitter = [33mtrue[0m }

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.flaky-result[0m

[3m(since 0.9.131)[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: Whether to treat flaky tests as passing or failing.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/features/retries/#failing-flaky-tests\Failing flaky tests]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m: [36m"pass"[0m, [36m"fail"[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"pass"[0m
- [1mExample[0m: [36mflaky-result = "fail"[0m

[1;4mTimeout configuration[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.slow-timeout[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (duration) or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Time after which tests are considered slow, plus optional
  termination policy.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/features/slow-tests/\Slow tests and timeouts]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m60s[0m with no termination on timeout
- [1mExamples[0m:
      slow-timeout = [32m"60s"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      slow-timeout = { period = [32m"120s"[0m, terminate-after = [33m2[0m, grace-period = [32m"10s"[0m }
      [2m# or[0m
      slow-timeout = { period = [32m"30s"[0m, terminate-after = [33m4[0m, on-timeout = [32m"pass"[0m }

The [36mslow-timeout[0m object accepts the following parameters:

- [36mperiod[0m: Time period after which a test is considered slow (required)
- [36mterminate-after[0m: Number of periods after which to terminate the test (default:
  do not terminate)
- [36mgrace-period[0m: Time to wait for graceful shutdown before force termination
  (default: 10s)
- [36mon-timeout[0m: [3m(since 0.9.115)[0m What to do when a test times out: [36m"fail"[0m (default)
  or [36m"pass"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.leak-timeout[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (duration) or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Time to wait for child processes to exit after a test completes.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/features/leaky-tests/\Leaky tests]8;;\[0m
- [1mExamples[0m:
      leak-timeout = [32m"100ms"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      leak-timeout = { period = [32m"500ms"[0m, result = [32m"fail"[0m }

