[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.bench.slow-timeout[0m

[3m(since 0.9.117)[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (duration) or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Time after which benchmarks are considered slow, plus optional
  termination policy. Replaces [36mslow-timeout[0m when running [36mcargo nextest bench[0m.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/features/benchmarks/\Running benchmarks]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: Unset
- [1mExamples[0m:
      bench.slow-timeout = [32m"120s"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      bench.slow-timeout = { period = [32m"60s"[0m, terminate-after = [33m10[0m, grace-period = [32m"10s"[0m }

The [36mbench.slow-timeout[0m object accepts the same parameters as [36mslow-timeout[0m:

- [36mperiod[0m: Time period after which a benchmark is considered slow (required)
- [36mterminate-after[0m: Number of periods after which to terminate the benchmark
