[1;4mReporter options[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.status-level[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: Level of status information to display during test runs.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/reporting/\Reporting test results]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m (incremental; each level includes those above it):
  - [36m"none"[0m: no output.
  - [36m"fail"[0m: only output test failures.
  - [36m"retry"[0m: output test retries; includes [36mfail[0m.
  - [36m"slow"[0m: output slow tests; includes [36mretry[0m.
  - [36m"leak"[0m: output leaky tests; includes [36mslow[0m.
  - [36m"pass"[0m: output passing tests; includes [36mleak[0m.
  - [36m"skip"[0m: output skipped tests; includes [36mpass[0m.
  - [36m"all"[0m: equivalent to [36m"skip"[0m today; reserved for future expansion.

- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"pass"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.final-status-level[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: Level of status information to display in the final summary.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/reporting/\Reporting test results]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m (incremental; each level includes those above it):
  - [36m"none"[0m: no output.
  - [36m"fail"[0m: only output test failures.
  - [36m"flaky"[0m: output flaky tests; includes [36mfail[0m. Accepts [36m"retry"[0m as an alias.
  - [36m"slow"[0m: output slow tests; includes [36mflaky[0m.
  - [36m"skip"[0m: output skipped tests; includes [36mslow[0m.
  - [36m"leak"[0m: output leaky tests; includes [36mskip[0m.
  - [36m"pass"[0m: output passing tests; includes [36mleak[0m.
  - [36m"all"[0m: equivalent to [36m"pass"[0m today; reserved for future expansion.

- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"flaky"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.failure-output[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: When to display output for failed tests.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/reporting/\Reporting test results]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m:
  - [36m"immediate"[0m: show captured output as soon as the test completes.
  - [36m"immediate-final"[0m: show captured output when the test completes [3mand[0m again at
    the end of the run.
  - [36m"final"[0m: show captured output only at the end of the run.
  - [36m"never"[0m: never show captured output.

- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"immediate"[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.success-output[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: When to display output for successful tests.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/reporting/\Reporting test results]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m: same as [36mfailure-output[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"never"[0m

[1;4mFailure handling[0m

[1;4m[36mprofile.<name>.fail-fast[0m

- [1mType[0m: Boolean or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Controls when to stop running tests after failures.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/running/#failing-fast\Failing fast]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: [36mtrue[0m (stop after first failure, wait for running tests to complete)
- [1mExamples[0m:
      fail-fast = [33mtrue[0m  [2m# Stop after first failure (waits for running tests)[0m
      fail-fast = [33mfalse[0m [2m# Run all tests[0m
      fail-fast = { max-fail = [33m5[0m }  [2m# Stop after 5 failures (waits for running tests)[0m
      fail-fast = { max-fail = [32m"all"[0m }  [2m# Run all tests[0m

      [2m# With termination mode (since 0.9.111)[0m
      fail-fast = { max-fail = [33m1[0m, terminate = [32m"wait"[0m }  [2m# Wait for running tests (default)[0m
      fail-fast = { max-fail = [33m1[0m, terminate = [32m"immediate"[0m }  [2m# Terminate running tests immediately[0m

When [36mmax-fail[0m is exceeded:

- [1m[36mterminate = "wait"[0m (default): nextest stops scheduling new tests but waits for
  currently running tests to finish naturally.
- [1m[36mterminate = "immediate"[0m [3m(since 0.9.111)[0m: nextest sends termination signals to
  running tests (respecting the grace period configured via
  [36mslow-timeout.terminate-after[0m).

