[1;4mScript configuration[0m

[3m(since 0.9.59)[0m

Scripts are configured under [36m[scripts.setup.<name>][0m and [36m[scripts.wrapper.<name>][0m
sections.

[1;4mSetup scripts[0m

[3m(since 0.9.98)[0m

For detailed information, see [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/setup-scripts/\Setup scripts[0m]8;;\.

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.command[0m

- [1mType[0m: String, array, or object
- [1mDescription[0m: The command to run for this setup script.
- [1mExamples[0m:
      command = [32m"echo hello"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      command = [[32m"cargo"[0m, [32m"run"[0m, [32m"--bin"[0m, [32m"setup"[0m]
      [2m# or[0m
      command = { command-line = [32m"debug/my-setup"[0m, relative-to = [32m"target"[0m }

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.slow-timeout[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (duration) or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Slow-timeout configuration for this setup script.
- [1mDefault[0m: No timeout
- [1mExamples[0m:
      slow-timeout = [32m"30s"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      slow-timeout = { period = [32m"60s"[0m, terminate-after = [33m1[0m, grace-period = [32m"5s"[0m }

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.leak-timeout[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (duration) or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Leak-timeout configuration for this setup script.
- [1mDefault[0m: [36m200ms[0m
- [1mExamples[0m:
      leak-timeout = [32m"500ms"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      leak-timeout = { period = [32m"1s"[0m, result = [32m"fail"[0m }

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.capture-stdout[0m

- [1mType[0m: Boolean
- [1mDescription[0m: Whether to capture stdout from this setup script.
- [1mDefault[0m: [36mfalse[0m

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.capture-stderr[0m

- [1mType[0m: Boolean
- [1mDescription[0m: Whether to capture stderr from this setup script.
- [1mDefault[0m: [36mfalse[0m

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.junit.store-success-output[0m

- [1mType[0m: Boolean
- [1mDescription[0m: Whether to store this setup script's output on success in the
  JUnit XML report.
- [1mDefault[0m: [36mtrue[0m

[1;4m[36mscripts.setup.<name>.junit.store-failure-output[0m

- [1mType[0m: Boolean
- [1mDescription[0m: Whether to store this setup script's output on failure in the
  JUnit XML report.
- [1mDefault[0m: [36mtrue[0m

[1;4mWrapper scripts[0m

[3m(since 0.9.98)[0m

For detailed information, see [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/wrapper-scripts/\Wrapper scripts[0m]8;;\.

[1;4m[36mscripts.wrapper.<name>.command[0m

- [1mType[0m: String, array, or object
- [1mDescription[0m: The command to run as the wrapper.
- [1mExamples[0m:
      command = [32m"my-script.sh"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      command = [[32m"cargo"[0m, [32m"run"[0m, [32m"--bin"[0m, [32m"setup"[0m, [32m"--"[0m]
      [2m# or[0m
      command = { command-line = [32m"debug/my-setup"[0m, relative-to = [32m"target"[0m }

[1;4m[36mscripts.wrapper.<name>.target-runner[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: How this wrapper composes with a configured target runner.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/features/target-runners/\Target runners]8;;\[0m
- [1mValid values[0m:
  - [36m"ignore"[0m: the target runner is ignored.
  - [36m"overrides-wrapper"[0m: when a target runner is configured, it replaces the
    wrapper; otherwise the wrapper runs as usual.
  - [36m"within-wrapper"[0m: the target runner runs within the wrapper script (command
    line: [36m<wrapper> <target-runner> <test-binary> <args>[0m).
  - [36m"around-wrapper"[0m: the target runner runs around the wrapper script (command
    line: [36m<target-runner> <wrapper> <test-binary> <args>[0m).

- [1mDefault[0m: [36m"ignore"[0m

[1;4mProfile script configuration[0m

[3m(since 0.9.59)[0m

Profile-specific script configuration under [36m[[profile.<name>.scripts]][0m sections.

[1;4mProfile script filters[0m

At least one of these filters must be specified.

[1;4m[36mplatform[0m

- [1mType[0m: String or object
- [1mDescription[0m: Host and/or target platforms these scripts apply to.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/specifying-platforms/\Specifying platforms]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: Scripts apply to all platforms
- [1mExamples[0m:
      platform = [32m"x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      platform = { host = [32m"cfg(unix)"[0m, target = [32m"aarch64-apple-darwin"[0m }

[1;4m[36mfilter[0m

- [1mType[0m: String (filterset expression)
- [1mDescription[0m: Filterset expression selecting tests these scripts apply to.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/filtersets/\Filterset DSL]8;;\[0m
- [1mDefault[0m: Scripts apply to all tests
- [1mExample[0m: [36mfilter = 'test(integration_test)'[0m

[1;4mProfile script instructions[0m

At least one instruction must be specified.

[1;4m[36msetup[0m

- [1mType[0m: String or array of strings
- [1mDescription[0m: Names of setup scripts to run (single name or array).
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/setup-scripts/\Setup scripts]8;;\[0m
- [1mExamples[0m:
      setup = [32m"my-setup"[0m
      [2m# or[0m
      setup = [[32m"setup1"[0m, [32m"setup2"[0m]

[1;4m[36mlist-wrapper[0m

- [1mType[0m: String
- [1mDescription[0m: Name of the wrapper script used during test listing.
- [1mDocumentation[0m: [34;4m[3m]8;;https://nexte.st/docs/configuration/wrapper-scripts/\Wrapper scripts]8;;\[0m
- [1mExample[0m: [36mlist-wrapper = "my-list-wrapper"[0m

[1;4m[36mrun-wrapper[0m

